      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"strategic refinement\" angle is a good start, but the reporter is going to be aggressive. They’re going to point out that the candidate literally said the exact opposite three weeks ago. If we just say we're \"evolving,\" they'll claim we're dodging the fact that we're reversing a core promise. Do we have any actual data or specific policy changes we can point to as the \"new information\" that triggered this, or are we just going to pivot on the rhetoric?",
